AGRICULTURE CODE

ground for removal exists, the executive director shall notify the
chairman of the state board. The chairman shall then notify the
governor and the attorney general that a potential ground for removal
exists. If the potential ground for removal involves the chairman,
the executive director shall notify the next highest ranking officer
of the state board, who shall then notify the governor and the
attorney general that a potential ground for removal exists.
Added by Acts 1985, 69th Leg., ch. 611, Sec. 12, eff. Sept. 1, 1985.
Amended by Acts 2001, 77th Leg., ch. 1095, Sec. 4, eff. Sept. 1,
2001.
Amended by:
Acts 2011, 82nd Leg., R.S., Ch. 61 (H.B. 1808), Sec. 3, eff.
September 1, 2011.

